text: Molly E.E. Wieland (born 1934), is a female former diver who competed for England. ==Diving career== She represented England and won a bronze medal in the 10 metres platform at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games in Cardiff, Wales. ==References== Category:1934 births Category:English female divers Category:Cyclists at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in diving Category:Commonwealth Games bronze medallists for England Category:Living people
